post_text:
We received word last night of three positive COVID-19 tests among Rams JV and Varsity football players. This brings the total number of lab-confirmed positive Rams football players to four.

As a result, we have made the difficult decision to cancel all football related events for our 9th grade, JV, and Varsity teams for the remainder of this week, including their games on Thursday and Friday. Since there are no known cases currently on the freshman team, they will play as scheduled.

We will do contact tracing today to identify individuals who have been in close contact with infected students. We will deep clean the field house, weight room, and athletic locker rooms today and will re-evaluate things this weekend regarding next week’s football activities.
text:
We received word last night of three positive COVID-19 tests among Rams JV and Varsity football players. This brings the total number of lab-confirmed positive Rams football players to four.

As a result, we have made the difficult decision to cancel all football related events for our 9th grade, JV, and Varsity teams for the remainder of this week, including their games on Thursday and Friday. Since there are no known cases currently on the freshman team, they will play as scheduled.

We will do contact tracing today to identify individuals who have been in close contact with infected students. We will deep clean the field house, weight room, and athletic locker rooms today and will re-evaluate things this weekend regarding next week’s football activities.

2020-21 Burro Senior Tribute Pages Available for Purchase Online

If you are interested in celebrating a senior this year with a Senior Tribute page in the yearbook, please go to www.balfour.com to reserve a page. There are 4 packages available. You can pay with credit/debit card or Paypal. Another option available is to email Mrs. Cryer at acryer@mwisd.net to purchase a page with cash, check, or money order. Reserve your page today!

FULL PAGE with Yearbook: $490
Max 120 Word Count, Max 10 Photos

½ PAGE with Yearbook: $295
Max 90 Word Count, Max 5 Photos

Max 60 Word Count, Max 3 Photos

1/8 PAGE with Yearbook: $140
Max 30 Word Count, Max 1 Photo

post_text: Mineral Wells ISD students and staff will pay tribute to the victims and heroes of September 11th as we pause to remember the nation’s grief in its losses and reflect upon the freedoms of our democracy. By commemorating 9/11, we are taking part in an important role of preserving the memory of those who were lost and honoring the sacrifices of first responders. We are so thankful for our teachers/staff, students, and our community and appreciate everyone joining us as we take a day to remember.

shared_text:
Melody Walden Singleton is with Mary Davis Michels and Beth Friedel Henderson.
August 26 at 7:53 AM ·

Y’all ! I’ve been thinking on the right words to express my gratitude......... then I realized there are not words to express such ! Being a “ School/Public Health Nurse” does not come with the Hero status that Hospital Nurses are receiving. We are more a Zero than a Hero! We look out for the good of all, which normally means we inconvenience a few 😢 Covid-19 has more than quadrupled this. Despite the negative view spewed on social media, two of God’s most humble servants gifted me with this ! While the gifts are loved, I covet their friendship MOST! Thank you both for being God’s Earth Angels ! You have lifted my head and my spirit 🙌🏼

The following video explains how a parent/guardian can submit their child’s daily wellness screening paperwork via Skyward.

Skyward Family Access will allow parents/guardians to submit the wellness screening online for each child prior to their arrival on campus every day. This is only for students that receive in-person instruction.

1. Go to the school website
2. Click the red "Skyward" button
3. Login with your user ID and password
4. Answer two simple questions about your child's health
5. Click save

Thank You!

Happy first week of school! Please mark your calendars. Mineral Wells ISD campuses will be closed on Friday, August 28th for a teacher workday. There will be no virtual or in-person instruction on that day.

Vacaciones estudiantiles el 28 de agosto

¡Feliz primera semana de escuela! Por favor, marque sus calendarios. Los campus de Mineral Wells ISD permanecerán cerrados el viernes 28 de agosto para una jornada laboral de maestros. No habrá instrucción virtual o en persona ese día.

Mineral Wells ISD
August 9 at 11:02 PM ·

MWISD has exciting news! We have partnered with TEAMFUNDED to offer reserved seating to ALL of our 2020 HOME football games! Skip the line, the hassle, the lost ticket scenario…SEEING YOUR RAMS PLAY JUST GOT EASIER!
$36 for six home games!

Link for tickets is listed below. After tickets are purchased online, the District will assign seating and contact the ticket holder for a scheduled pick-up time a week before the first football game.

*Stadium capacity will be at 50 percent

*Once ticket limit is reached, ticket sales will end

*Past ticket holders will not have their traditional seating. (Those seats will be saved for the 2021 football season)

*Every other row and social distancing will be maintained

*Parking passes will be available for all six games for only $20

*COVID-19 UIL guidelines are available on the school website

Ready to buy your reserved seating or a parking pass?
Click this link: https://mw.payments.school/

shared_text:
Mineral Wells Police Department
August 17 at 9:14 PM ·

Here at the MWPD we know how awesome all our student’s parents are. We know you’ve got them adjusted to a back to school sleep schedule 😴, and have been limiting screen time to make room for enriching end of summer activities 🕹. And we know you’re all busy packing a nutritionally balanced Pinterest worthy bento box lunch 🍱, setting out ironed and perfectly coordinated outfits with matching masks 👕, and tucking your children into bed where they wait eagerly to wake up well rested before your alarm goes off when they will have their hair and teeth brushed dressed and ready for the full breakfast you will cook them 🥓🍳🥞....ok but seriously even if you have to tell them to wake up 637 times and throw a granola bar at them while pulling them out of the house in mismatched shoes you’re still awesome.

We wanted to remind you that with school starting up, school zones will also be active again. Please remember our school zones are active the entire day with a 20mph speed limit and no cell phone use while driving. Our officers will be patrolling school zones to keep our kids safe!

post_text:
MWISD Wants to see your First Day of School Photos!

We are so excited to welcome back our students tomorrow for the first day of the 2020-2021 school year! Regardless if you are joining us through online instruction or in person, Mineral Wells ISD knows how much preparation goes into that first day of school- school supplies, an outfit, a haircut, a backpack, the classroom, the lesson plans, and most importantly, the first day of school photo!

So why not show it off? Snapping that first day of school photo at home, on your front porch, at the bus stop, or in front of the school is a tradition for our students, parents, and staff.

Submit photos on your Facebook or Twitter page with the hashtag #mwisdmatters. It is a fun and easy way to celebrate our students, staff, and parents’ smiles on the first day of school.

Keep in mind if you use a hashtag in a post you share, your settings must be set to public to show up in that hashtag's feed. Tag your photos with #mwisdmatters.

shared_text:
John Kuhn
August 14 at 3:08 PM ·

MWISD Parents:

Please note that parent drop off lines are often longer the first weeks of school because many bus parents choose to bring their kids to school to get the year started. This year, we will have fewer kids riding buses due to Covid-19 concerns, so the drop off lines might be longer. This may be offset by the fact that many students are learning from home.

I write this to encourage you to arrive a good 10 minutes earlier than you normally would to allow time to get through the line. Also please know that things always settle in after the first two weeks and dropoff times decline sharply after people adjust arrival times and learn the routines.

Mineral Wells ISD
July 27 at 4:31 PM ·

2020-21 Online & In-Person Student Registration

This year, MWISD offers online and in-person student registration. To register online, visit www.mwisd.net and click on the red “Skyward” button. After entering your login information, please select the “2020-21 Returning Student Information Verification” button on the left side of the screen.

Mineral Wells ISD will also offer on-site registration for K-12th grade on Monday, August 3rd from 10:00 am – 6:00 pm. This is a come and go event at the high school. Should you decide to come to the school to complete the registration process, please look for clearly marked entry and exit areas. Social distancing will be required and the governor’s order on masks/ facial coverings will be observed during on-site registration.

If you have any questions regarding registration, please call the Registration Hotline at (940) 328-0065. We hope you are having a great summer and we are looking forward to the start of a new school year. Go Rams!

post_text:
The application for P-EBT will be extended until July 31, 2020.

Because of school closures from COVID-19, Texas received approval from the U.S. Department of Agriculture to provide more than $1 billion in pandemic food benefits to families with children that have temporarily lost access to free or reduced-price school meals.

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) provides eligible families with a one-time payment for each child who previously received free or reduced-price meals. P-EBT works the same way Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP) benefits do and will help families get the food they need during the current pandemic. P-EBT will be administered by the Texas Health and Human Services Commission, Texas Department of Agriculture and Texas Education Agency.

https://www.yourtexasbenefits.com/Learn/PEBT?fbclid=IwAR12voioyuGuuLvF-KX28FdcA8gD0s0Ykyz3-wQINu0Htcd-V40l87scP5A

2019-2020 Auxiliary Employee of the Year is Janalee Martin

Janalee Martin -----"She is always full of positivity and has mastered offering support and encouragement to challenge teachers to incorporate technology. She is on my campus often and has nothing by nice things to share about teachers. She has tried many different platforms, contests, and professional development opportunities so that teachers can try something with their own comfort level. I have seen her in multiple classrooms, on her knees, down with students and co-teaching in the classroom. I hear rave reviews from the teachers that have worked with her and we continually add more and more teachers that are willing to book her to try something new". Congratulations to Janalee!

2019-2020 MWISD Support Employee of the Year is Jasmin Meza

"Jasmin is the sweetest most helpful para. She was willing to take a position this year as an MCL aide with new expectations and demands and no additional pay. She works just as hard as a teacher. She has learned quickly from watching her MCL and doesn’t hesitate to jump in and teach any of the 1st grade classrooms that need help. She is supportive of all our students. Multiple times I have seen her working one-on-one with a student. She is bilingual and often helps supports teachers by helping with parents calls and translating. She does this all with a smile on her face. My plan is to encourage her to go to college to become a teacher, because she is already a natural! Congratulations Jasmin"!

-Lamar Elementary

post_text:
The Power of Three-

Carla Purdue, Family Nurse Practitioner from PPGH presented Telehealth Connections, a new service for MWISD that is designed to connect schools, nurses, and healthcare providers by providing primary care access using technology to ensure that every child has a chance at good health and a good education.

Beginning in the fall of 2020, every MWISD nurses’ office will have a telehealth station that will offer on-demand access to care providers for things like a nagging cough, sniffle or infection that would otherwise necessitate a phone call and a family’s inconvenient trip to the doctor’s office.

Using the equipment, MWISD Lead Nurse, Wanda Voelcker demonstrated how a nurse would connect to a care provider. TeleHealth Connections Agent, Scott McCray was on-hand to answer the call. Nurses will be able to discuss a student’s symptoms, medical issues, and more with a healthcare provider in real-time.

TeleHealth Connections will be a valuable tool to assist our professional school nurses to provide additional school health services to our students.

June 4th Chromebook Return

Travis Parents,

The school year comes to a close on Wednesday, May 27th. This year we have a few other details to work out that are much different than other years. We are scheduling June 4th, from 2-6 pm to take care of Chromebook return. This will be in the front drive at Travis. We will accept Travis Chromebooks only and ask that you remain in your vehicle as always. During this time, we will also offer medicine pickup for those that were left with the nurse. If your child left personal belongings in their locker those can be picked up at this same time. I thank you for a wonderful and eventful school year that we will remember forever. We will all grow and be stronger people from the events of this year. I wish you a safe and happy summer break.

Thank you,

David Wells
Principal
Travis Elementary
Mineral Wells ISD

post_text:
SUMMER FEEDING FLYER
JUNE-JULY 2020

Mineral Wells ISD will continue to provide nourishing meals Monday thru Friday for students and Backpack Buddies will provide weekend meals.

Below are the dates, times and place to pick up meals.
It will be "grab n go-drive thru" meal service during the month of June. At the end of June, MWISD will announce food service plans for July.

If you have any questions please call:

Carrie Davis
Food Service Director
940-327-5133.

Summer Feeding Program at Travis Elementary

Any child ages 0-18 or still in school gets free meals.
Your child does not have to be a MWISD student.

Monday, June 1st thru Friday, July 24th.
We will be closed Friday, July 3rd.
Weekend meals will be handed out on Thursday, July 2nd.

Grab 'n Go Drive Thru Pickup at Travis Elementary
Pick up from 10:30 am to 12:30 pm
No delivery service will be provided. Breakfast and lunch provided daily and Weekend meals provided on Friday.

2020 Senior Tribute Begins Today, May 10th

S & K Automotive has gone the extra mile to celebrate our Mineral Wells High School seniors amid the Covid-19 pandemic.

Duke and Jessica Samples felt compelled to celebrate our 2020 seniors in a big way! Beginning today, the public can visit “Senior Row” at Mineral Wells High School.

It begins on the corner of 180 & Industrial Boulevard and runs the length of the thoroughfare. After the in-person graduation on Saturday, June 6th, S&K is donating these special keepsakes to each student.

It is an amazing sight to see! Thank you again to S & K for this wonderful addition to our senior celebration!

Tonight, MWHS recognized the top 10 percent of the graduating class of 2020 with a special curbside celebration. Each student received their honor cords and a yard sign for their home.

MWISD is proud of our elite students and their commitment to academic excellence. They are remarkable representatives of our Ram Family, and we are excited about how they will continue to find success in each of their unique purposes as they begin the next chapter of their education.

The 18 academic leaders making up the 2020 top ten percent are as follows:

Valedictorian Kishan Patel, Salutatorian Paige Riney, Sasha Kirsch (not pictured), Emma Bullock, Reagan Carter, Hailey Tincher, Declan Williams, Lacoda Davis, Abel Aragon, Alondra Villegas, Kortney Rincon, Rian Schultz, Samantha Lopez, Mallory Howard (not pictured) Claire Rasmussen, Kloie Sherrod, Elijah Batchelor, and Jessie Ishmael. Congratulations!

https://youtu.be/Yfol0zNyXIE

post_text:
2020 Senior Ram Walk
Senior Celebration Posters, Signs, and Banners

Help us recognize all the hard work our seniors have put in this year and let's cheer them through to the finish line.

MWHS invites seniors, families, friends, and community members to make senior posters, signs, and banners to display down Ram Boulevard.

MWHS Seniors will be scheduled in shifts to arrive at the high school May 11-18, 2020 to video their senior walk. We want to have a big collection of congratulatory signs lining Ram Boulevard that will welcome our students as they arrive at the school. Families may personalize their signs with messages of encouragement, ribbons, college, military, or career plans, or whatever you feel will make your graduating senior feel special.

Keep in mind that signs will need to be up from May 11th until May 29th. Please make sure your outdoor signs are securely displayed. Signs may be attached to high school track fence if needed.

El gobernador de Texas, Greg Abbott, anunció el 17 de abril una Orden Ejecutiva enmendada que pedía que todas las escuelas de Texas permanecieran cerradas hasta el final del año escolar. Esto significa que las instalaciones de Mineral Wells ISD permanecerán cerradas y todos los eventos y actividades se cancelarán hasta finales de mayo. MWISD ha creado la siguiente página en nuestro sitio web que se dedica a las preguntas frecuentes y nuestras respuestas sobre los planes de fin de año del Distrito.

post_text:
Signing Day 2020 is Here!

Deciding where you’re going to college is exciting. It’s a major step toward a person’s future, and it should feel like an epic occasion. Whether it is a community college, university, a certification program, the military, or any other education past high school, College Signing Day shows support for this future.

Mineral Wells High School scheduled the Class of 2020 College Signing Day for Friday, April 17th. Amidst the challenges COVID-19 has brought to our lives, we still want to recognize our seniors on this special day. The path one chooses to life after high school is a momentous decision and one that deserves to be celebrated, even in challenging times. Congratulations to our seniors! #bettermakeroom

https://youtu.be/oiTO1Wl1VB8

shared_text:
Cassandra Jackson is with Trudy Browning and 10 others.
April 9 at 10:40 AM ·

Fun. Love. Laughter. Dedication. Dress up days. Learning. Exploring. Making memories. Laying the foundation for years to come.

This is my family.
This is my home away from home.
These are my people, little and big.

It’s times like these that really remind you to have an attitude of gratitude.

I’m grateful for the laughter, memories, and all my students have achieved this year. Grateful for the dedication from my administration (shoutout to our incredible APs, Marshall & Dianna Leggett), they’re working tirelessly. Grateful for our SPED staff for working so hard to meet student needs. Grateful to be a part of a district, who sprang in to action to take care of all of our children in the community - even though they weren’t walking our halls each day.

#lovemyschoolday
#mwisdmatters
#ramstrong

shared_text:
Melissa Campbell Selby is with Leslee Medlin Barham and Patti Johnson Breeden.
April 9 at 4:07 PM ·

As many of you know I am a first year teacher. I didn’t go the traditional route because it took me a little while to listen to what God had for me. I had given up on the idea of teaching because I hadn’t found a spot. God had different plans though. One day in October I got the call and interview that changed my life. Suddenly I had an entire new family through Mineral Wells ISD. Administrators who took a chance on hiring me and have been so patient with me. An entire staff who are so sweet and encouraging. A team of teachers who took me in and welcomed me with open arms. A mentor, Leslee, who has guided, loved, and taught me more than she knows. Last, but most definitely not least are my kids! All 10 of them hold a special place in my heart, and I love them like they were my own. I miss them terribly and I just hope they know that they were so worth the wait! I can’t wait to see all of them soon! But until then...#mwisdmatters #lovemyschoolday

Building relationships with families is near and dear to my heart as well as with my school family! Mineral Wells is Blessed with so many that have a heart for teaching, collaborating and desire to make things happen even during uncertain times! I am thankful to all the parents who have partnered with us to help keep students on target with their learning! We know it is not easy and we appreciate all you are doing! It has been amazing to see how our district has come together with the change. Our administration, teachers, staff, and students are all doing the best they can and it's been amazing to see.

I cannot wait to see my coworkers, which have become my family, and students again when this is all over! Stay strong and healthy!!

#lovemyschoolday
#mwisdmatters

shared_text:
Helen Strawbridge Bull
April 3 at 12:59 PM ·

Students that will be sending in the tryout videos for MWHS Wranglerettes please remember you have till 4/25 to send in yours. See our FB page for tryout dance video. Email hbull@mwisd.net for music. Take your time practicing. You want to send in the best tryout possible. Practice the techniques separately: X jump, press leap, kicks, splits, double pirouettes, leap and toe touch. You do NOT have to be perfect in all these. We are looking for students that can move to music, can keep time, and show Potential. 😊Showmanship is a big factor: smile, have fun, be a PERFORMER.🎶 The judges and I can't wait to see you dance. Include your full name and grade at beginning of your video. Friends please pass this on to reach as many students as possible.

I made a Padlet for my high school students last week (it's a digital bulletin board) and asked them their favorite thing about no school/social distancing. I have loved reading every response! Almost all have said things like family time, rest, quality time with family, cleaning, reading, being creative. Although I miss them like crazy, I'm encouraged that they are seeing the positive in being unplugged from the craziness of life for a time. #seniors2020 #mwisdmatters #ramstrong

PRIMARYPLAYGROUND.NET
Scavenger Hunts - Primary Playground

Lamar Elementary
April 1 at 9:33 AM ·

Hello Lamar Families!

With our district still adjusting to learning at home, we want to make sure you are taking time to
spend some time outdoors in your backyard or on your porch. There are many things your children can learn just by being outside. If you’re looking for a twist, try a scavenger hunt!

Scavenger hunts can be modified for indoors or out, and you can put an academic spin on them. Use sticky
notes to place letters, numbers, shapes or sight words around your house or outside.

Don’t have sticky notes? Regular squares of paper with tape work just as well.

Happy Learning!
Lamar Prekindergarten

Used with permission from Primary Playground

https://primaryplayground.net/scavenger-hunts/?fbclid=IwAR1SbculT9_4LSNpEGSUtWXIGlwxHX6zUE8HLmXG9-BW02KK1N9p4NRhbJc

Scavenger hunts can be modified for indoors or out, and you can put an academic spin on them. Use sticky
notes to place letters, numbers, shapes or sight words around your house or outside.

Don’t have sticky notes? Regular squares of paper with tape work just as well.

Happy Learning!
Lamar Prekindergarten

shared_text:
Mineral Wells ISD added 299 new photos.
March 28 at 1:59 PM ·

In this era of social distancing and quarantine, it would be difficult for photographers to take family portraits. So, on "Feel Good Friday", MWISD teamed up with Fryer Photography and set up a free “Curbside Family Photo Booth” for our students as they drove thru at Travis Elementary.

Fryer helped set up a photo shoot area, measured off 6 feet from the car to the sidewalk, and started taking photos to any family that was interested. The results were amazing! Some sweet, some hilarious, but all incredible memories for these families to share. It was a great opportunity to document this time in their lives. One day when these kids are grown up, they're going to be able to look back at this time and talk about it. Thank you to Fryer Photography for your help as we try to continue to send a message of positivity in our community. Also a special shout out to Jessie Ishmael for the Sonic drinks!

shared_text:
John Kuhn
March 22 at 6:38 PM ·

Special thank you to principals, APs, nurses, MCLs, office support staff, and DSC helpers, along with Coaches Hobbs and Jones and others for rushing into the breach today and helping us to pass out work packets to over 600 kids at Travis, 400 at Houston, hundreds at JH, and 85,000 at Lamar.

Thank you parents for your patience and good humor. We’ve never done anything like this before, and we will have 2 weeks to work out any kinks if we aren’t back in school by then. We couldn’t have done it without the support of our parents today.

I love this town.

Tomorrow we start something brand new. MWISD is here for our students even in this new reality. Go Rams and Ram family!

John Kuhn
March 19 at 2:10 PM ·

IMPORTANT: A parent with a medically fragile person in the home asked if we will have a way to distribute packets electronically so people don’t have to leave the home.

Yes!

Each campus is handling this differently. Travis will be emailing all parents tomorrow. (If you don’t get the email, it may be that your email in Skyward isn’t correct. Please check that.)

Houston is posting something to their FB page today about this.

Lamar says to contact your homeroom teacher to request it.

For HS and JH, please email ccarter@mwisd.net to request an electronic packet.

Also I saw a link to a packet that was shared online by someone today. I don’t know what that packet was, but I’m certain it wasn’t MWISD’s work, which is still being put together at this time.

Hope this helps.

George King and Jerome Jackson are the newest members of the Mineral Wells High School Athletic Hall of Fame after their inductions during halftime of the Rams' basketball game against Brownwood tonight. The two former all-staters took their games to the next level at the University of North Texas and Midwestern State University respectively. Jackson led MSU to a 53-11 mark over two seasons and is in the school's Hall of Fame. King still holds UNT's three-point career shooting percentage average.

post_text:
It has Been a Wonderful Ride!

It is surreal to think that our seniors’ basketball career will conclude on Tuesday, February 11th. It will be the culmination of an amazing journey for these four Lady Rams.
We are looking forward to enjoying the game where they step onto the court one last time with their teammates and coaches.

In honor of our seniors, a special senior display will be set up outside the gym doors for the public to view. The seniors will be recognized AFTER their home game vs. the Brownwood Lady Lions at 6:15 pm. There will be a special half-time recognition by Jerry Hamilton and the Mineral Wells Hall of Honor and free t-shirts to the first 100 Ram Fans! Remember it is "White Out Night" so wear your favorite Ram spirit gear and pack the stands to cheer on our teams.

The Mineral Wells High School would like to invite the public to attend the Ram Expo on Monday, January 27 from 5:30-7:00 P.M in the cafeteria.

The Ram Expo is for upcoming 9th-12th grade students. Hope Mesler will discuss high school graduation requirements and endorsements. Dr. Funk will be explaining Honors, Advanced Placement and dual credit at 5:30, 6, 6:30.

Teachers will be available to discuss graduation options and electives. We are also excited that Dr. Sarah Locke from Weatherford College will discuss dual credit at 5:30, 6 and 6:30 in the tiered lecture hall and a representative from Tarleton State University will discuss the new exciting opportunities for MWHS students.

We hope to see you there!

You are cordially invited to the 94th Annual MWHS Coronation on Saturday, February 1, 2020 at 8:00 pm in the High School Auditorium. This year's theme is “Enchanted Garden” .

This magical evening will be spent honoring our high school royalty, enjoying our talented student entertainment, and dancing the night away at the Royal Ball. Tickets go on sale at the high school office on Monday, January 27th and you must have a ticket to attend the dance.

Pictured is King Lacoda House of Davis and Queen Jaycelyne House of Jacobo.

MWISD invites the public and all Tarleton State University alumni from the Mineral Wells area to attend a special meeting of the Mineral Wells ISD Board of Trustees to be held on January 6th at 6 pm in the MWHS cafeteria.There will be a short meeting followed by a small reception and celebration. Tarleton State University officials, including new TSU President Dr. James Hurley, plan to be in attendance.

The purpose of the meeting is for the board to vote on a proposed Memorandum of Understanding between MWISD and Tarleton State University that will benefit many MWHS graduates for years to come and will deepen the already strong relationship between our two institutions.

I have only heard glowing reports about your students today when they visited Bass Hall for a performance of the Nutcracker. Everyone was so impressed at how polite and attentive they were during the performance. We were so happy they got here for the pre-show experience. In fact, the ballet dancers were SO impressed with the questions your students asked and how respectful they were during the demonstrations. Thank you so much for your hard work in making the experience a good one for everyone.

Happy Holidays!

Sue Buratto
Director of Education

text:
Mineral Wells Index is with Harold Fisher.
December 16, 2019 at 2:50 PM ·

Ram Rescue Readers from Mrs. Pierce’s Travis Elementary School reading class went to the Mineral Wells Texas Animal Shelter and read to animals there. They also brought donations to help make the animals’ stay a better one.

post_text:
The Ram Rescue Readers from Travis Elementary are hoping to make a huge difference for animals at the Mineral Wells Animal Shelter.

Students from Travis Elementary were very excited to get to read to an animal of their choice at the shelter today. They each selected a book and brought a seat cushion.

Many of the shy shelter animals responded positively as the students read to them. It was a great way to simply share the same reading experience they themselves love.

Be sure to check out the Mineral Wells Index this week for the entire story!

For more information or to provide a forever home to one of these animals, please contact the Mineral Wells Shelter at 940-328-7752.
text:
The Ram Rescue Readers from Travis Elementary are hoping to make a huge difference for animals at the Mineral Wells Animal Shelter.

Students from Travis Elementary were very excited to get to read to an animal of their choice at the shelter today. They each selected a book and brought a seat cushion.

Many of the shy shelter animals responded positively as the students read to them. It was a great way to simply share the same reading experience they themselves love.

Be sure to check out the Mineral Wells Index this week for the entire story!

For more information or to provide a forever home to one of these animals, please contact the Mineral Wells Shelter at 940-328-7752.
